                       Irish Studies | Irish Studies Program | Catholic University   
                                                       About the Center  Undergraduate Program  Graduate Program  Study Abroad  Events & Lectures                  Gala Celebrates Ireland with Special Tribute to William J. Flynn Over 300 friends of the William J. Flynn Center for Irish Studies attended the annual Irish Gala on Nov. 4 at the Houstonian Hotel for a Gala raising more than $270,000 for student scholarships. Read more      Center Appoints Irish Language Scholar The University of St. Thomas William J. Flynn Center for Irish Studies has appointed Jonathan O’Neill, MA as an Irish Studies scholar. Originally from Counties Galway and Clare in Ireland, O’Neill joins the Center from the University of Limerick. Read more      Gallagher Receives Recognition for Her Irish Education Work Lori Gallagher, J.D., was recognized among the 2-14 Irish Education 100 by Irish Voice, an Irish American newspaper and magazine. The award recognizes educators at top universities and institutions across the nation who promote Irish and Catholic success in education. learn more      Study Abroad Explore the coasts of Ireland and Northern Ireland on study abroad with the William J. Flynn Center for Irish Studies. Ride a bike on the windswept rocky coasts, and recall the Irish blessing, “May the road rise to meet you.” learn more    
           Irish Student Life 
  Join the Irish Club, take Irish language courses, study abroad in Ireland and Northern Ireland or earn a Minor or Master of Liberal Arts graduate concentration in Irish Studies. come see         Support the Center 
  The William J. Flynn Center for Irish Studies is one of a kind in the Southwest. Learn how to get involved with the Center.    learn more         Events & Lectures 
  The Center sponsors lectures and cultural events, such as St. Patrick’s Day, storytellers and lively concerts.
  come see             
       
Spring 2017 Irish Studies Courses
The Flynn Center for Irish Studies is offering scholarships of $750 to the first 10 students who sign up and qualify for scholarships for each of the following spring 2017 courses. A student may be eligible for more than one scholarship (if one signs up for more than one).
 Complete the scholarship application  Before completing the application, review the qualifications for students who are interested in applying.   Irish Gaelic Literature in Translation
